textBox.richText: We hope that today will be the last moving out day. The crew here today is focused and on a mission to finish the job. I can’t say that it is difficult to see all our possessions pass through the open doors and into the huge truck parked in front of our house. I am happy with our decision to leave Princeton. Still there’s something that tugs at the heart. Closing this phase of life, but the next phase not yet begun -- living in a holding pattern with no visible landing strip.
